cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the capacity of channels with feedback and derives new evaluation methods to extract graph-based encoders with their achievable rates. 
2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper mentions the use of auxiliary directed graphs in the evaluation method. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is another possible category as the paper deals with communication channels and their capacity. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper mentions the use of a coding scheme based on the posterior matching principle. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possible category as the paper deals with the performance of feedback systems.
